50|$|Interventionism is {{a policy}} of non-defensive (proactive) {{activity}} undertaken by a nation-state, or other geo-political jurisdiction of a lesser or greater nature, to manipulate an economy and/or society. The most common applications of the term are for economic interventionism (a <b>state's</b> <b>intervention</b> in its own economy), and foreign interventionism (a <b>state's</b> <b>intervention</b> {{in the affairs of}} another nation as part of its foreign policy).|$|R
